<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Witch1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Witch,</orth> subst. 1) a woman who practises sorcery: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.258" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 258</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.258" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 258</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.269.258" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 269</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 88</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 88</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 88</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 88</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 88</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.120" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.120" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 120</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 1.2.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 2, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.149" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 149</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.149" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 149</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 4.3.80" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.4.151" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 151</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.186" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 186</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.5.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 5, 6</bibl> (one who could draw a witch's blood was free from her power). <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.5.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 5, 6</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.38" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.34" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 2, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 2, 75</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.172" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 172</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.4.72" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 4, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 1, 46</bibl> <cit><quote>(thou stool for a w.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 6</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.23" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 23</bibl> <cit><quote>(--es' mummy).</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.163" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 163</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.2.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 2, 37</bibl> <emph>(the w. take me, if I meant it thus).</emph><lb />Term of reproach for an old and ugly woman: <cit><quote>a mankind w.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 67</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the cripple tardy-gaited night who like a foul and ugly w. doth limp so tediously away,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV Chor.</bibl></cit> 21; <bibl n="shak. tro 4.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 2, 12</bibl>. <cit><quote>foul wrinkled w.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.164" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 164</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the w. shall die,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 4.12.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 12, 47</bibl></cit>.
<lb />2) a male sorcerer: <cit><quote>I could find in my heart to stay here still and turn w.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 4.4.160" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 4, 160</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>out, fool, I forgive thee for a w.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 40</bibl></cit> (cf. the proverb: <emph>you'll never be burnt for a witch</emph>). <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 166</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>